Do you therefore consider the adoption of this law to be a benefit or an additional burden for the administration?
I believe that this law is a step in the right direction and I hope that the future will confirm it.
The problem that may arise is that these rules become more stringent and it is not possible to comply with them.
Already under the previous regulations, the provider (e.g. the Regional Council, in the case of regional operational programmes) forced controlled subjects to accept that any breach of the contract law meant a breach of budgetary discipline.
Is it really useful to make the law more severe in this way?
No, not that way, I think.
The system must exclude those who want to attack or abuse the system but not punish those who make formal mistakes without consequences for the decision-making process.
