However, the cult of the fatherly figure of the nation, a man who has led his country as a dictator, knows almost no limits in Azerbaijan.
He was in power until 2003, after which his son Ilham succeeded him.
In any event, the elderly in Azerbaijan do not experience distress.
Mirzayeva receives 230 manats a month (about the same amount as in euros) for his retirement, a sum that guarantees a good lifestyle in the region.
And perhaps Mirzayeva's long-grey son is right: "The elders enjoy great respect in our culture".
They are the center of the great family, they are loved, cared for and happy.
